9. A buffer is temporary memory used to hold data while it is being moved from 
one place to another. buffers are used when there is a difference in the rate 
at which data is received and the rate at which it can be processed.

12. scaling up generally means upgrading a system to a more powerful system.  
whilst scaling out means adding systems. although it is reasonable to assume 
that scaling up and scaling out could have the same effects it is highly 
circumstantial.

